FBIS4-32583 "dreeu124_h_94007" FBIS-EEU-94-124 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 HUNGARY State Assets Agency Chairman Resigns State Assets Agency Chairman Resigns LD2806073694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 0700 GMT 28 Jun 94 LD2806073694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Hungarian BFN [Text] Tibor Pongracz, chairman of the board of directors of the State Assets Agency [AVU], has resigned. The state secretary for privatization is the fourth member of the board of directors to step down from his position. The 11-member body has thereby decreased in size to seven. Tibor Pongracz told NEPSZABADSAG that the prime minister accepted his resignation with effect from 1 July. The AVU's board of directors is still capable of making decisions because six members are sufficient for decisionmaking.
